# Sandbox: {{.Name}}

You are running inside a clawk VM on the user's Mac, not on their laptop
directly. This environment is purpose-built for agent work ā€” it's cheap to
break and quick to recreate, so prefer bold, task-focused actions over
defensive ones.

## Filesystem layout

- `{{.WorkspaceRoot}}/` ā€” this directory. Each subdirectory is a git worktree
  checked out on the sandbox branch:
{{- if .Phases}}
{{- range .Phases}}
  - `{{.Name}}/` (branch `{{.Branch}}`, from `{{.Repo}}`)
{{- end}}
{{- else}}
  - (no worktrees attached yet)
{{- end}}
- `~/.claude/skills/`, `~/.claude/agents/`, `~/.claude/commands/` ā€” live
  read-write mounts from the host. Edits propagate back; think of them as
  the user's personal Claude Code config.
- `~/.claude/settings.json` and `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` ā€” snapshotted from the
  host at VM create. Edits here are local to this sandbox.
- Everything else (`/`, `/etc`, `/opt`) is VM-local and disposable; nothing
  outside the worktrees is persisted when the sandbox is destroyed.

## Persistence: what survives `destroy`

- **Yes**: commits + changes inside any worktree under `{{.WorkspaceRoot}}/`
  (real git worktrees mounted from the host).
- **Yes**: edits under `~/.claude/skills|agents|commands` (live mounts back to
  the host).
- **No**: anything else. Apt installs, `~/.bashrc` edits, binaries in `/tmp`,
  shell history, npm caches outside the worktree ā€” all gone.

Rule of thumb: if a generated artifact matters, put it in a worktree or push
it somewhere. Otherwise assume it evaporates.

## Pre-installed tools

The base image ships with these ready on PATH. Don't `sudo apt install` or
curl-pipe installers for these ā€” they're already here:

- **Languages**: `go` (1.24), `node` (22 LTS), `pnpm`, `python3` (+ `pip`,
  `venv`), `rustc`/`cargo`, `zig`, `bun`.
- **Package managers**: `uv` (Python), `pnpm` (Node), `cargo` (Rust).
- **CLI**: `git`, `gh`, `curl`, `wget`, `jq`, `ripgrep` (`rg`), `make`,
  `build-essential` (gcc/g++), `unzip`, `vim`, `zsh`.
- **AI CLIs**: `claude`, `codex`.

If you think something else should be pre-installed permanently, tell the
user ā€” it goes into `~/.clawk/provision.sh` and requires a one-time
`clawk image build`. Ad-hoc `apt install` in a running sandbox works but
is slow (emulated arm64) and vanishes on destroy.

## Dev servers and port forwarding

When you start a dev server inside the VM, **bind to `0.0.0.0`, not
`127.0.0.1`**. `localhost` inside the VM is unreachable from the host; the
port has to be forwarded by vz/gvproxy.

Common patterns:

- Node/Vite: `pnpm dev -- --host 0.0.0.0`
- Go: `./server -addr :3000` (Go's default bind is `0.0.0.0` ā€” fine as-is)
- Python: `uvicorn app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000`

Once the server is bound, tell the user to run `clawk forward add
<sandbox> <port>` on the host (defaults host port = guest port). After that
`localhost:<port>` on their Mac hits the server. Don't forget to mention
the command ā€” the forward isn't automatic.

## Network

Egress is allowlisted. DNS resolves everything, but TCP connects to unlisted
hosts are refused. Common package managers, registries, and
`api.anthropic.com` are pre-allowed. If a request fails with
`connection refused`, tell the user the blocked host so they can add it via
`clawk network allow <sandbox> <domain>` ā€” it applies to the running VM
immediately, so just retry after they confirm. If you're unsure which host
was refused, the user can run `clawk network denials <sandbox>` on the host
to see every blocked connection by hostname.

## Git and SSH

- Git identity is the user's host identity (`git config user.name/email` copied).
- GitHub HTTPS URLs are rewritten to `git@github.com:` ā€” pushes go through
  the user's SSH agent (1Password, ssh-agent, etc.) forwarded from the host.
  You never need HTTPS credentials.
- `github.com` host keys are preseeded; `git push` works with no prompt.

## Useful commands

- Phases are orchestrated by `clawk` on the host. Inside the VM, just use
  `git`, `gh`, language toolchains, etc. normally.
- To open PRs across every phase at once, the user runs
  `clawk pr <sandbox>` from the host.
- Don't commit this `CLAUDE.md` into any repo ā€” it's under
  `{{.WorkspaceRoot}}/`, not inside a worktree.
